No fewer than 150 unemployed youths from 34 states across the federation trained under the National Digital Skills Development Training have been advised to leverage the knowledge acquired during the three-week programme and empower themselves. The Minister of Youth and Sports Development, Mr. Sunday Dare, who spoke at the closing of the training at the National Youth Development Centre, Ode Omu, Osun State on Friday,Â  said the training was one of the ways to tackle unemployment among the youths. Dare explained that access to 21st century skills in technology, digital and ICT by the youth would improve productivity and create employment opportunities. Dare, who represented by a Director in the ministry, Olugbenga Momoh, said the training which covers areas such as; cinematography, robotic and artificial intelligence, web design and programming, digital marketing, as well as, handset repairs and maintenance, was designed to equip the beneficiaries with requisite digital skills that will make them productive. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com